                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d187">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/24472: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Mexicali</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Boyle</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexicali</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-08-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 18, 1920</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received August 19—3:42 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Governor Cantu this afternoon, as forecasted, delivered the reins of government
                    over to Luis M. Salazar and thus brought to a termination the state of factional
                    strife threatened in this district.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Boyle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
